<TITLE> Release of Khaleda at final stages: adviser </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 9 (bdnews24.com)  The procedure to release BNP chief Khaleda Zia is at final stages, education adviser Hossain Zillur Rahman said on Saturday. "The result is likely very soon. Many problems of BNP will be resolved as soon as Khaleda Zia is freed," Zillur told reporters after inaugurating a government project at Local Government Engineering Department. Asked about the status of the release of the former prime minister, the adviser said: "The government has made its position clear on the matter during the release of another former prime minister Sheikh Hasina." "There were some problems, which are being resolved to ensure the release procedure." On the government's dialogue with the BNP, he said: "The government is in contact with the BNP. We hope to conclude the procedure soon." The adviser also spoke on the government's position on the Awami League's statement that it would not participate in any elections amid the state of emergency and its demand for national elections ahead of to all other polls. Hossain Zillur said: "The government is going to hold the second round of dialogue with the Awami League very soon. The party is eager to discuss the two issues there." The government will convince the AL in the dialogue on the issues, he said. "The government will take all decisions in consultation with the parties all parties will have to be persuaded." "The government is holding formal and informal talks with them," the adviser said. bdne
